1
00:00:00,188 --> 00:00:01,753
Previously, on
"Grey's Anatomy"...

2
00:00:01,783 --> 00:00:04,247
She cut his LVAD wire.

3
00:00:04,359 --> 00:00:07,134
Denny Duquette died
at 7:42 this evening.

4
00:00:07,226 --> 00:00:09,677
I had a baby and I went soft.

5
00:00:09,791 --> 00:00:12,741
Your hand is fine,
and Shepherd will clear you for surgery.

6
00:00:13,006 --> 00:00:15,370
- Our marriage is over.
- Yeah, I guess it is.

7
00:00:15,445 --> 00:00:17,864
Who am I to you, George?
Am I your girlfriend?

8
00:00:17,979 --> 00:00:19,406
Am I somebody you
mess around with?

9
00:00:19,436 --> 00:00:20,625
Can I buy you a drink, Callie?

10
00:00:20,655 --> 00:00:22,570
Only if you have it
delivered to my hotel room,

11
00:00:22,602 --> 00:00:23,608
because I'm off to bed.

12
00:00:23,631 --> 00:00:26,504
- You are a great guy.
- So it's Derek.

13
00:00:26,626 --> 00:00:28,803
He's gonna hurt you again.
I'm walkin' away.

14
00:00:28,936 --> 00:00:30,723
It's for you. It's from Denny.

15
00:00:36,275 --> 00:00:38,111
<i>First do no harm--</i>

16
00:00:38,727 --> 00:00:41,591
<i>As doctors,
we pledge to live by this oath.</i>

17
00:00:42,775 --> 00:00:46,062
<i>But harm happens...
and then guilt happens.</i>

18
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:48,790
<i>And there's no oath for
how to deal with that.</i>

19
00:00:49,187 --> 00:00:49,932
Morning.

20
00:00:50,046 --> 00:00:52,593
I thought we were done with
the whole muffin thing.

21
00:00:52,596 --> 00:00:55,010
This isn't muffins.
This is breakfast.

22
00:00:55,175 --> 00:00:57,463
Mer needs a good,
solid breakfast.

23
00:00:57,737 --> 00:00:59,841
First day back after
the big surgery.

24
00:00:59,956 --> 00:01:00,910
Are you okay?

25
00:01:01,187 --> 00:01:02,283
Of course I'm okay.

26
00:01:02,465 --> 00:01:04,221
I'm a millionaire. Fruit?

27
00:01:05,705 --> 00:01:07,402
What do you guys
think about B&Bs?

28
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:09,392
I'm thinking about
opening a B&B in Vermont

29
00:01:09,436 --> 00:01:10,891
where the foliage is, you know?

30
00:01:10,926 --> 00:01:12,313
Maybe you should
go back to bed.

31
00:01:12,348 --> 00:01:14,321
Can't. I'm going
to the hospital.

32
00:01:14,428 --> 00:01:15,631
Are you gonna go
talk to the chief?

33
00:01:15,665 --> 00:01:17,941
Nope. Going to
clean out my locker.

34
00:01:18,377 --> 00:01:21,171
I could buy a hotel.
How much do you think a hotel costs?

35
00:01:22,297 --> 00:01:23,330
- Izzie
- Is that...

36
00:01:24,175 --> 00:01:25,541
That is $8 million.

37
00:01:26,327 --> 00:01:28,583
$8 million does not like to
have juice spilled on it.

38
00:01:28,617 --> 00:01:30,091
You have to take that
to the bank today.

39
00:01:30,127 --> 00:01:31,691
It's making me
nervous in the house.

40
00:01:31,727 --> 00:01:33,830
I will,
as soon as I clean out my locker.

41
00:01:35,736 --> 00:01:36,811
I am fine.

42
00:01:37,007 --> 00:01:38,712
Really, I am fine.

43
00:01:39,415 --> 00:01:40,550
Denny loved me.

44
00:01:40,917 --> 00:01:42,390
He wanted me to
have this money.

45
00:01:42,425 --> 00:01:43,712
He wants me to be happy.

46
00:01:44,318 --> 00:01:45,413
So I'm happy.

47
00:01:46,017 --> 00:01:46,992
Juice?

48
00:01:50,598 --> 00:01:51,772
She's losing it.

49
00:01:51,897 --> 00:01:55,781
She almost battered and deep fried an
$8 1/2-million check this morning.

50
00:01:56,127 --> 00:01:58,403
That kind of money,
I'd buy my own hospital

51
00:01:58,496 --> 00:02:00,141
and stock it full
of sick people.

52
00:02:00,326 --> 00:02:03,613
Valvuloplasties and
ruptured aneurysms... mm.

53
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:05,861
You're a psycho.
You know that, right?

54
00:02:05,897 --> 00:02:08,893
I'm not the one with an $8
1/2-million check I won't cash.

55
00:02:09,027 --> 00:02:11,783
Stop talking about me.
I'm fine.

56
00:02:12,335 --> 00:02:14,811
I am cleaning out my locker
and I am going home.

57
00:02:15,325 --> 00:02:17,241
Mer is the one
with the problems.

58
00:02:18,615 --> 00:02:19,833
What's wrong with me?

59
00:02:20,698 --> 00:02:23,251
Well, now you haven't told
McDreamy that you dumped McVet.

60
00:02:23,288 --> 00:02:24,573
Oh, you haven't done that yet?

61
00:02:24,606 --> 00:02:25,613
Dude, tell him already.

62
00:02:25,648 --> 00:02:27,961
- She's scared.
- I am not scared.

63
00:02:28,076 --> 00:02:30,242
Derek walked away.
He walked away.

64
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:31,562
And maybe that's a good thing.

65
00:02:31,595 --> 00:02:32,941
I mean, maybe he's happier.

66
00:02:33,027 --> 00:02:34,031
Maybe he's moved on.

67
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:36,070
He's got Addison here,
he's got Mark here.

68
00:02:36,105 --> 00:02:37,951
He's... got a lot to deal with.

69
00:02:38,146 --> 00:02:39,641
And I'm not gonna
make him feel guilty.

70
00:02:39,676 --> 00:02:41,770
I mean,
I am being an adult here.

71
00:02:41,906 --> 00:02:44,300
And I am not going to drag
him into our whole...

72
00:02:46,338 --> 00:02:48,602
Izzie is the one
with the big check.

73
00:02:49,478 --> 00:02:50,453
I'm fine.

74
00:02:50,857 --> 00:02:53,832
Guilt never goes
anywhere on its own.

75
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:57,422
It brings its friends
doubt and insecurity.

76
00:03:01,487 --> 00:03:02,930
Is that your boyfriend again?

77
00:03:03,055 --> 00:03:04,763
I do not have a boyfriend.

78
00:03:05,326 --> 00:03:06,753
Then why the guilty face?

79
00:03:07,428 --> 00:03:09,472
You were sexier when
you weren't talking.

80
00:03:10,355 --> 00:03:12,261
Am I keeping you, O'Malley?

81
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:16,703
M&M in 15 minutes, people.

82
00:03:16,835 --> 00:03:18,733
Wait,  wait, wait.
We get to go to M&M?

83
00:03:18,736 --> 00:03:19,970
Even if we haven't
finished our rounds?

84
00:03:20,006 --> 00:03:22,530
Even if.
I want all of you to the M&M today.

85
00:03:22,745 --> 00:03:23,712
Yes!

86
00:03:24,808 --> 00:03:27,232
People die in this
hospital on our watch.

87
00:03:27,455 --> 00:03:29,852
Once a month,
we meet to discuss how our actions

88
00:03:29,905 --> 00:03:32,082
as physicians contributed
to the deaths.

89
00:03:32,297 --> 00:03:33,922
This is a serious exercise.

90
00:03:34,025 --> 00:03:35,001
Dr. Bailey.

91
00:03:37,248 --> 00:03:38,601
George, Alex,
you guys get good seats,

92
00:03:38,636 --> 00:03:39,932
Mer and I will get snacks.

93
00:03:40,077 --> 00:03:41,421
Uh, Mr. and Mrs. Niles.

94
00:03:41,627 --> 00:03:43,270
We kinda got turned around
on our way to admitting.

95
00:03:43,307 --> 00:03:44,402
Oh, oh, not a problem.

96
00:03:44,507 --> 00:03:48,943
Dr. Karev, uh, Mrs. Niles is
scheduled for a mastectomy tomorrow.

97
00:03:49,097 --> 00:03:51,602
Uh, why don't you show her and
her husband up to the fifth floor?

98
00:03:51,637 --> 00:03:53,120
Is this the little man?

99
00:03:53,777 --> 00:03:55,292
He is adorable.

100
00:03:55,418 --> 00:03:56,800
He's not so adorable
at 4:00 in the morning

101
00:03:56,837 --> 00:03:58,453
when he's screaming and
won't take a bottle.

102
00:03:58,485 --> 00:03:59,883
Can we just get to the room?

103
00:04:00,348 --> 00:04:01,891
It's been kind of a rough week.

104
00:04:02,038 --> 00:04:04,021
She had to stop nursing.
Gus here just won't eat.

105
00:04:04,058 --> 00:04:05,773
Here. Why don't I take you up?

106
00:04:06,488 --> 00:04:07,380
There you go.

107
00:04:07,986 --> 00:04:10,932
You know, you can try a little
sugar water on the bottle,

108
00:04:11,048 --> 00:04:13,240
just until he gets used to it.

109
00:04:15,448 --> 00:04:17,191
Does that woman
have breast cancer?

110
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:18,762
What is she, 30 years old?

111
00:04:18,876 --> 00:04:19,802
It's a new baby.

112
00:04:19,916 --> 00:04:22,070
Probably thought the
lump was a milk duct.

113
00:04:23,685 --> 00:04:25,473
You learn things on
the vagina squad.

114
00:04:25,505 --> 00:04:26,673
Okay, yeah, focus, people.

115
00:04:26,716 --> 00:04:29,903
M&M--insults flying,
residents covering their asses,

116
00:04:30,118 --> 00:04:32,760
our bosses getting kicked
in the teeth instead of us.

117
00:04:33,156 --> 00:04:34,472
Seats, then snacks.

118
00:04:36,997 --> 00:04:39,470
Hey. I didn't know you
were coming to the M&M.

119
00:04:40,327 --> 00:04:41,273
You brought snacks?

120
00:04:41,435 --> 00:04:43,100
Well... yeah.

121
00:04:45,436 --> 00:04:47,110
- You okay?
- Fine.

122
00:04:47,447 --> 00:04:49,083
Hey, no surgeries today, right?

123
00:04:49,218 --> 00:04:51,112
I mean, I'm ready if you need me.
- No.

124
00:04:52,498 --> 00:04:53,672
No surgeries.

125
00:05:01,338 --> 00:05:03,631
Callie. Hey.

126
00:05:04,175 --> 00:05:07,033
Hi. Did you get my message--
my messages?

127
00:05:07,277 --> 00:05:08,522
Yeah. I gotta get a seat.

128
00:05:08,627 --> 00:05:11,271
Alex  is saving us a bunch
if you want to sit with us.

129
00:05:20,346 --> 00:05:22,743
She's trying to make me feel
guilty about the other night,

130
00:05:22,775 --> 00:05:23,960
about the Izzie thing.

131
00:05:24,818 --> 00:05:27,811
- I thought you said you apologized already?
- I did. I have.

132
00:05:28,297 --> 00:05:31,460
I'm done.
I-I am not apologizing anymore.

133
00:05:32,137 --> 00:05:34,433
I'm enjoying life.
I'm loving the M&M.

134
00:05:34,865 --> 00:05:36,891
Okay, people, let's begin.

135
00:05:37,355 --> 00:05:42,910
Patient 34986 died last month from
complications following a
heart transplant.

136
00:05:43,137 --> 00:05:44,843
Dr. Burke will present.

137
00:05:49,388 --> 00:05:53,823
- You guys... isn't patient 34986...
- Denny.

138
00:05:54,007 --> 00:05:55,103
$8 million...

139
00:05:55,645 --> 00:06:00,000
$8 million could get us on a
plane to somewhere far, far away.

140
00:06:26,927 --> 00:06:28,921
Cause of death at
autopsy was an embolus

141
00:06:29,008 --> 00:06:31,651
that dislodged from the
suture line of the transplant

142
00:06:31,865 --> 00:06:34,360
and caused a C.V.A.
with brain stem herniation.

143
00:06:34,457 --> 00:06:35,262
Dr. Burke?

144
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:38,748
So the company line is
that he died of a C.V.A.?

145
00:06:38,891 --> 00:06:41,294
There's no company line.
That's what he died of.

146
00:06:41,896 --> 00:06:43,763
Uh, yes,
let's get back to this, uh,

147
00:06:43,935 --> 00:06:46,140
patient's need for an
emergent transplant.

148
00:06:46,606 --> 00:06:51,940
You're saying that his left ventricle
had been weakened by the
LVAD malfunction?

149
00:06:52,095 --> 00:06:56,013
His left ventricle was weakened by the fact
that he suffered from congestive heart failure.

150
00:06:56,048 --> 00:06:57,672
Oh, come on, Dr. Burke.

151
00:06:58,195 --> 00:07:00,853
We all know the LVAD
was cut by an intern.

152
00:07:01,358 --> 00:07:02,953
Oh, I'm going to
my happy place.

153
00:07:02,985 --> 00:07:04,642
The exact chain of
events remain unclear.

154
00:07:04,678 --> 00:07:08,370
It remains unclear to you because you're
in the E.R. with a gunshot wound.

155
00:07:08,767 --> 00:07:10,773
Why aren't we hearing
from Dr. Bailey?

156
00:07:10,966 --> 00:07:12,662
She was the senior
physician on the case.

157
00:07:12,697 --> 00:07:14,182
I am the attending on record.

158
00:07:14,378 --> 00:07:17,942
Yes... I was the
resident in charge.

159
00:07:28,706 --> 00:07:32,563
Dr. Burke has summarized the
medical facts of this case.

160
00:07:32,795 --> 00:07:34,520
Are there any questions for me?

161
00:07:37,795 --> 00:07:40,932
Grey's Anatomy - Saison 3 Episod 5
"Oh, The Guilt"

162
00:07:42,186 --> 00:07:44,890
You recently had a baby,
Dr. Bailey?

163
00:07:45,687 --> 00:07:47,363
I don't see what that
has to do with--

164
00:07:47,395 --> 00:07:49,941
Sleep deprivation coupled with
wild swings in hormone levels

165
00:07:49,977 --> 00:07:52,321
are factors that could
cloud anyone's judgment.

166
00:07:52,768 --> 00:07:54,790
I sleep just fine, Dr. Savoy.

167
00:07:54,965 --> 00:07:58,231
Really? 'Cause if a patient died
due to my poor decision making,

168
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:00,841
I'd probably lose at least
a little sleep or it.

169
00:08:00,876 --> 00:08:04,791
Let me remind everyone that our
purpose here is not to place blame.

170
00:08:05,098 --> 00:08:09,381
This is a forum to discuss mistakes
in patient care and learn from them.

171
00:08:09,488 --> 00:08:12,310
Well, so far, I haven't heard Dr.
Bailey admit to a mistake.

172
00:08:12,345 --> 00:08:15,101
Why don't they just put a
bullet in the back of her head?

173
00:08:15,137 --> 00:08:16,591
It would be more humane.

174
00:08:16,727 --> 00:08:18,371
So for a period
of several hours,

175
00:08:18,716 --> 00:08:22,172
your interns were running amok in
the hospital, totally unsupervised.

176
00:08:23,236 --> 00:08:24,670
I'm waiting for a question.

177
00:08:24,787 --> 00:08:26,720
The question is where were you?

178
00:08:27,956 --> 00:08:31,472
There was the shooting, and the E.R.
was chaotic.

179
00:08:31,588 --> 00:08:32,843
The E.R. is always chaotic.

180
00:08:32,878 --> 00:08:34,411
Did you page them
during this time?

181
00:08:34,446 --> 00:08:36,651
Yes, I paged them
multiple times.

182
00:08:36,797 --> 00:08:39,993
Well, apparently, they thought it
was okay to ignore your pages.

183
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:44,473
Doctor, why do you think your interns
have such contempt for your authority?

184
00:08:44,577 --> 00:08:46,623
You don't know what the
hell you're talking about!

185
00:08:46,658 --> 00:08:47,990
Dr. Karev, sit down.

186
00:08:56,855 --> 00:08:57,701
I zzie.

187
00:09:03,826 --> 00:09:05,773
Next question.

188
00:09:06,588 --> 00:09:09,983
Derek says that neither of you
brought any assets into the marriage.

189
00:09:10,647 --> 00:09:14,011
Well, I had my trust fund and
a sparkling personality...

190
00:09:15,158 --> 00:09:16,290
And the futon couch.

191
00:09:16,445 --> 00:09:19,411
Yes, Addison had a very ugly,
very heavy futon couch.

192
00:09:19,536 --> 00:09:20,863
What ever happened
to that couch?

193
00:09:20,896 --> 00:09:21,951
We gave it to Mark.

194
00:09:22,336 --> 00:09:24,193
- She can have him.
- I don't want him.

195
00:09:24,228 --> 00:09:25,751
Okay, well, that's settled.
What else?

196
00:09:25,787 --> 00:09:28,990
So aside from Addison's trust fund,
which remains in her name,

197
00:09:29,268 --> 00:09:32,462
you'll split everything--
stocks, bonds, 401ks--down the middle.

198
00:09:32,766 --> 00:09:35,603
The only that gets a little
complicated is the real estate.

199
00:09:35,638 --> 00:09:37,553
Let me make this, uh, simple.

200
00:09:37,705 --> 00:09:40,303
I'd like to keep my trailer
and the land in Seattle.

201
00:09:40,338 --> 00:09:41,712
Addison can have the rest.

202
00:09:41,898 --> 00:09:42,823
Hold on.

203
00:09:42,956 --> 00:09:44,313
That's the house
in the hamptons

204
00:09:44,345 --> 00:09:45,930
and the brownstone
overlooking Central Park?

205
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:47,450
- That's very generous, Dr. Shepherd.
- Thank you.

206
00:09:47,485 --> 00:09:50,263
- Hold on. He's up to something.
- No, I'm not.

207
00:09:50,408 --> 00:09:53,883
I came here to fight over cds and books,
go to war over a crystal vase.

208
00:09:53,916 --> 00:09:54,993
What are you up to, Derek?

209
00:09:55,025 --> 00:09:56,220
The divorce is my fault.

210
00:09:56,248 --> 00:09:58,360
- Let me take responsibility.
- We both had affairs.

211
00:09:58,397 --> 00:10:00,190
You had a one-night
stand with Mark.

212
00:10:01,396 --> 00:10:02,820
Derek, actually...

213
00:10:03,308 --> 00:10:05,652
- well, it was--
- Oh, okay, it was two nights.

214
00:10:05,807 --> 00:10:06,911
You  made a mistake.

215
00:10:08,137 --> 00:10:10,033
Meredith and I,
we had a relationship.

216
00:10:10,386 --> 00:10:12,531
Make these changes,
and I'll sign it today.

217
00:10:15,998 --> 00:10:18,110
You weren't supposed
to be in here, Izzie.

218
00:10:18,255 --> 00:10:19,860
You shouldn't have
had to see that.

219
00:10:19,897 --> 00:10:22,680
No, it's fine. I'm fine.

220
00:10:23,736 --> 00:10:26,600
Clearly the doctor thing
was not working for me.

221
00:10:27,606 --> 00:10:29,170
So go about your business.

222
00:10:29,385 --> 00:10:31,443
Run labs, cure cancer.
I'm fine.

223
00:10:31,808 --> 00:10:33,142
You're not going home.

224
00:10:33,988 --> 00:10:36,682
Either you hang out with us
or we'll call your mother.

225
00:10:37,856 --> 00:10:39,312
She's just a few hours away,

226
00:10:39,447 --> 00:10:42,840
and I'm sure she wouldn't mind coming
and staying with you, all day.

227
00:10:44,087 --> 00:10:45,641
- You wouldn't.
- Dialing.

228
00:10:48,217 --> 00:10:49,291
I'll just...

229
00:10:50,447 --> 00:10:52,142
go hang out in the locker room.

230
00:11:07,555 --> 00:11:10,672
What is she doing here?
She has no business in this room.

231
00:11:13,677 --> 00:11:15,222
What are you looking at me for?

232
00:11:15,576 --> 00:11:17,520
I didn't have anything
to do with this.

233
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:20,010
I didn't have anything
to do with any of this.

234
00:11:21,038 --> 00:11:23,210
I'll stay with her today,
if that's okay.

235
00:11:23,387 --> 00:11:25,751
I'll update charts
and I'll run labs

236
00:11:25,927 --> 00:11:28,120
and just keep an eye on her,
if that's okay.

237
00:11:28,138 --> 00:11:31,083
-  She shouldn't be alone.
- Fine.

238
00:11:33,517 --> 00:11:34,891
Dr. Bailey...

239
00:11:35,107 --> 00:11:36,661
- We just wanna say...
- We're really sorry...

240
00:11:36,695 --> 00:11:40,833
- About the M&M.
- No, you do not get to apologize to me for this.

241
00:11:40,926 --> 00:11:42,912
You do not get to feel better.

242
00:11:43,275 --> 00:11:44,461
Neither do I.

243
