I have to tell George.

486
00:24:26,778 --> 00:24:30,592
Honey, please, at least hold Gus.
No, don't-- stop it.

487
00:24:30,735 --> 00:24:33,830
- Will you at least talk to me?
- I want you to leave me alone.

488
00:24:39,447 --> 00:24:41,572
You took a lot of hits
today at that M&M.

489
00:24:42,075 --> 00:24:45,143
Some of 'em justified,
some of 'em not.

490
00:24:45,795 --> 00:24:50,030
Compassion and empathy
are a big part of the job.

491
00:24:50,175 --> 00:24:51,921
Look, I don't care
what Savoy said,

492
00:24:52,568 --> 00:24:54,941
and I know I haven't
always been supportive,

493
00:24:56,696 --> 00:25:00,960
but being a parent makes
you a better doctor.

494
00:25:15,596 --> 00:25:19,162
Hi. I just... wanted to say hi.

495
00:25:21,306 --> 00:25:24,973
Denny left me $8 million--
$8.7 million to be exact.

496
00:25:25,107 --> 00:25:28,213
Did you know that he had money?
'Cause I didn't know.

497
00:25:28,746 --> 00:25:30,403
No, I didn't know.

498
00:25:31,457 --> 00:25:33,353
I'm thinking about
using it to travel,

499
00:25:33,607 --> 00:25:36,531
maybe go to Italy. I've never been
there before. I hear Venice is amazing.

500
00:25:36,567 --> 00:25:38,321
- Izzie--
- I'm fine.

501
00:25:38,687 --> 00:25:40,083
Really, I am. I'm fine.

502
00:25:40,747 --> 00:25:43,092
Everyone thinks I'm not.
Everyone thinks I'm...

503
00:25:43,677 --> 00:25:45,083
but I'm fine.

504
00:25:45,937 --> 00:25:50,773
You're fine. I'm fine.
Everything's fine.

505
00:25:53,298 --> 00:25:55,520
- So...
- I got shot.

506
00:25:57,368 --> 00:26:01,042
I got shot because I was coming back
to the hospital to check on Denny.

507
00:26:02,547 --> 00:26:04,790
Because you told me to.

508
00:26:05,696 --> 00:26:07,232
I'm not fine.

509
00:26:07,855 --> 00:26:13,313
Denny asked you to marry him,
and now he is dead. You're not fine.

510
00:26:13,457 --> 00:26:15,042
Don't come in here and...

511
00:26:18,456 --> 00:26:22,860
just... we're not fine.

512
00:26:25,028 --> 00:26:26,480
I'm sorry.

513
00:26:27,726 --> 00:26:29,243
We were friends.

514
00:26:29,347 --> 00:26:31,021
You were my boss, but...

515
00:26:31,347 --> 00:26:33,363
I think we were friends, too.

516
00:26:34,307 --> 00:26:36,002
And--and I never meant...

517
00:26:37,217 --> 00:26:38,693
for anyone to get hurt.

518
00:26:39,125 --> 00:26:41,883
And I know there is nothing
I can do to take it back.

519
00:26:43,126 --> 00:26:44,423
No.

520
00:26:44,977 --> 00:26:47,360
Preston, please--

521
00:26:47,516 --> 00:26:51,950
You quit. You quit...
being a surgeon.

522
00:26:52,818 --> 00:26:54,890
You have two good hands...

523
00:26:55,836 --> 00:26:57,871
and you aren't using them.

524
00:26:58,406 --> 00:27:00,550
Feel guilty about that.

525
00:27:10,617 --> 00:27:12,812
Sonja, quit grabbing my leg.

526
00:27:12,925 --> 00:27:15,581
I am not grabbing you anywhere.
She is.

527
00:27:15,728 --> 00:27:19,523
Mr. Morris, we need to position you
correctly in order to get a clear image.

528
00:27:20,826 --> 00:27:23,052
Dr. Yang,
move him a little to the left.

529
00:27:27,526 --> 00:27:28,970
Hey. What are you doing here?

530
00:27:29,027 --> 00:27:33,041
Oh, I heard about it.
I had to see it.

531
00:27:35,167 --> 00:27:36,713
And I've seen enough.

532
00:27:36,925 --> 00:27:39,893
Dr. Yang, I need you to lift
him a little as you pull him.

533
00:27:40,026 --> 00:27:41,132
Trying.

534
00:27:42,115 --> 00:27:45,062
Now lift his right
leg 20 degrees.

535
00:27:47,138 --> 00:27:47,942
Pain!

536
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:49,533
Freeze! Hold that position.

537
00:27:49,636 --> 00:27:54,601
Okay, now, Dr. Grey, can you kind
of slowly swirl Mrs. Kellman

538
00:27:54,745 --> 00:27:56,633
in a
counterclockwise direction?

539
00:27:56,767 --> 00:27:58,553
Swirl? Swirl?

540
00:27:58,698 --> 00:28:00,551
Swirl. Swirl.

541
00:28:05,475 --> 00:28:07,061
Oh, my god, Sonja.

542
00:28:07,186 --> 00:28:09,100
Oh, god, Adam. Not now.

543
00:28:09,187 --> 00:28:11,260
- Careful. Careful.
- Oh, my god.

544
00:28:11,446 --> 00:28:13,431
- Oh, my god.
- Okay, now, Grey, Yang,

545
00:28:13,616 --> 00:28:17,423
on the count of three, I want you
to slowly, gently pull them apart.

546
00:28:17,546 --> 00:28:20,492
One, two, three.

547
00:28:22,536 --> 00:28:24,132
Oh, okay. He's having a--

548
00:28:24,305 --> 00:28:25,331
Sonja!

549
00:28:25,668 --> 00:28:27,441
Heart attack!
He's having a heart attack!

550
00:28:27,478 --> 00:28:29,671
Oh, thank god.
I mean, code blue.

551
00:28:30,816 --> 00:28:32,592
Oh, he's tearing
through his aorta.

552
00:28:32,825 --> 00:28:35,041
We need to get him to an O.R.
now, or he's gonna die.

553
00:28:35,076 --> 00:28:37,121
Who's the cardiothoracic
surgeon on call?

554
00:28:37,128 --> 00:28:38,610
Dr. Harrison.
But he's in the middle of surgery.

555
00:28:38,647 --> 00:28:39,591
Where's Burke?

556
00:28:40,306 --> 00:28:42,522
He's in the conference room,
but he's not on the board yet.

557
00:28:42,555 --> 00:28:45,422
Well, he is now. Notify the O.R.
Let's move, people.

558
00:28:45,516 --> 00:28:46,870
Come on. Go, go, go.

559
00:28:56,268 --> 00:28:57,180
How do we do this?

560
00:28:57,275 --> 00:28:58,421
You stand on my right side.

561
00:28:58,455 --> 00:28:59,383
On your right side...

562
00:28:59,416 --> 00:29:01,072
and if at any time
during the procedure--

563
00:29:01,107 --> 00:29:01,921
if you tremor...

564
00:29:02,007 --> 00:29:05,960
I'll look at you. You'll know to slide
in to do the sutures we've practiced.

565
00:29:07,586 --> 00:29:10,562
What if one of the scrub nurses notices?
What if they say something?

566
00:29:10,596 --> 00:29:13,063
Cristina, I can't walk
away from this surgery.

567
00:29:13,736 --> 00:29:15,532
If I do,
that man in there will die.

568
00:29:15,577 --> 00:29:18,280
So tremor or no tremor,
I have to try.

569
00:29:18,576 --> 00:29:19,463
But you--

570
00:29:19,555 --> 00:29:23,961
I'm your intern.
I will be there on your right side.

571
00:29:42,415 --> 00:29:43,423
10 blade.

572
00:29:54,005 --> 00:29:57,652
As soon as we hear something about
your ex-husband, we'll let you know.

573
00:29:57,785 --> 00:30:01,610
Since I removed your I.U.D.,
you may want to use a backup method.

574
00:30:01,796 --> 00:30:06,220
Oh, I doubt I'll be having sex
anytime soon once I tell Tom.

575
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:10,861
You're--you're gonna
tell your husband?

576
00:30:11,756 --> 00:30:15,401
You know, the first time it happened,
I felt so guilty,

577
00:30:15,698 --> 00:30:19,272
and I wasn't gonna tell Tom because
it was never gonna happen again.

578
00:30:20,375 --> 00:30:24,013
And then it happened
again and again.

579
00:30:25,668 --> 00:30:29,921
And then somewhere along the way,
I just stopped feeling guilty.

580
00:30:30,987 --> 00:30:34,481
Yeah... I'm gonna
tell my husband.

581
00:30:36,727 --> 00:30:40,423
I think the truth just has to come out,
you know?

582
00:31:04,987 --> 00:31:06,673
Dr. Burke,
I know it's a lot to ask,

583
00:31:06,705 --> 00:31:10,351
but I would really appreciate if you'd
let me try my running whip stitch.

584
00:31:17,866 --> 00:31:19,881
All right, take a good bite.

585
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:23,463
You want to make
sure it holds. Good.

586
00:31:23,875 --> 00:31:25,463
Don't put too much pressure.

587
00:31:27,805 --> 00:31:29,951
There. Keep going.

588
00:31:33,365 --> 00:31:35,313
Oh, my god.

589
00:31:35,477 --> 00:31:38,720
Cristina's doing a running
whip stitch on a heart.

590
00:31:38,827 --> 00:31:41,253
I guess sleeping with
your boss has its perks.

591
00:31:41,838 --> 00:31:45,100
This sucks.
Cristina gets sex and perks.

592
00:31:45,457 --> 00:31:47,972
Maybe you should just
apologize again, George.

593
00:31:48,075 --> 00:31:51,470
Yeah, 'cause you're in a great
position to give relationship advice.

594
00:31:53,296 --> 00:31:57,171
Cristina's doing a running
whip stitch on a heart.

595
00:32:02,786 --> 00:32:04,413
I don't feel like talking.

596
00:32:09,348 --> 00:32:13,853
When I'm driving home at night
after a long day at work,

597
00:32:14,297 --> 00:32:17,730
all I can think about
is getting to my baby.

598
00:32:18,598 --> 00:32:20,372
If this is where you tell
me to fight the cancer

599
00:32:20,405 --> 00:32:22,251
so I don't miss out on
the joys of motherhood--

600
00:32:22,285 --> 00:32:25,421
Then I get home--
the baby's crying...

601
00:32:27,527 --> 00:32:34,981
the exhaustion hits, and I resent that
tiny baby's presence in my house,

602
00:32:35,605 --> 00:32:39,611
my previously very quiet house.

603
00:32:39,747 --> 00:32:41,282
Why are you telling me this?

604
00:32:41,756 --> 00:32:43,602
So you know what I do?

605
00:32:44,578 --> 00:32:47,552
First, I pick a fight
with my husband,

606
00:32:47,646 --> 00:32:51,092
you know, blame him for
not settling the baby down,

607
00:32:51,256 --> 00:32:54,700
then I bitch about the
neighbors' loud music.

608
00:32:54,827 --> 00:33:02,973
And if I'm really tired and
pissed off... I blame the baby.

609
00:33:05,747 --> 00:33:08,460
I mean,
if you hadn't been breast-feeding,

610
00:33:08,585 --> 00:33:13,111
you never would've thought the
lump was a clogged milk duct.

611
00:33:13,698 --> 00:33:17,651
You would've gone to the
doctor as soon as you felt it,

612
00:33:18,007 --> 00:33:20,341
the cancer wouldn't
have gotten this far,

613
00:33:20,566 --> 00:33:23,491
and you wouldn't be here
making this decision.

614
00:33:25,505 --> 00:33:27,261
Am I close?

615
00:33:30,427 --> 00:33:33,941
What kind of mother blames
her own baby for her cancer?

616
00:33:34,358 --> 00:33:40,103
A mother who's human.
A mother who's overwhelmed.

617
00:33:43,307 --> 00:33:46,683
But if this is gonna kill me eventually,
wouldn't it be easier

618
00:33:46,827 --> 00:33:49,170
if it happed when
Gus was little?

619
00:33:49,286 --> 00:33:52,270
Wouldn't it be easier for
him if I just never existed?

620
00:33:53,127 --> 00:33:59,071
Now this is the part when I
tell you to fight the cancer

621
00:33:59,218 --> 00:34:03,431
so that you don't miss out
on the joys of motherhood.

622
00:34:05,445 --> 00:34:06,580
Derek.

623
00:34:06,718 --> 00:34:08,010
Hey, you know what I like?

624
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:10,563
I like that we're civilized.

625
00:34:10,737 --> 00:34:14,192
We're these adult, grown-up people
who can be divorced and friendly.

626
00:34:14,337 --> 00:34:15,640
We deserve a medal.

627
00:34:15,747 --> 00:34:17,741
- It wasn't a one-night stand.
- What?

628
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:21,191
Mark and I-- it wasn't a one-night
stand. I was in love with him.

629
00:34:21,645 --> 00:34:23,901
Or... at least,
I thought I was.

630
00:34:24,676 --> 00:34:27,580
After you left,
we lived together for two months.

631
00:34:27,656 --> 00:34:29,772
I wanted to believe that
we could make it work,

632
00:34:29,807 --> 00:34:34,580
that I hadn't thrown my marriage away,
that I hadn't thrown my life away on a fling.

633
00:34:35,478 --> 00:34:38,802
But he's Mark, and, well...

634
00:34:39,028 --> 00:34:41,571
I caught him with
someone else, and...

635
00:34:42,458 --> 00:34:44,410
and then Richard called...

636
00:34:45,638 --> 00:34:48,530
We both had relationships
with other people.

637
00:34:48,647 --> 00:34:54,142
We're both equally liable for everything,
so please take the brownstone.

638
00:34:54,855 --> 00:34:56,710
All I want is Seattle.

639
00:34:56,835 --> 00:35:00,363
I want Seattle,
and I want never to see you again.

640
00:35:23,448 --> 00:35:29,323
You're here. You're everywhere,
and I can't not tell you.

641
00:35:30,675 --> 00:35:36,262
You know, I've been... not telling you
all day because I thought it was kind,

642
00:35:36,375 --> 00:35:38,731
and I thought I was
giving you space.

643
00:35:38,856 --> 00:35:43,292
But I can't not tell you because
you're here and you're you and...

644
00:35:45,265 --> 00:35:47,693
I broke up with Finn.

645
00:36:06,496 --> 00:36:07,590
I told you.

646
00:36:17,466 --> 00:36:19,500
The operation was successful.

647
00:36:19,656 --> 00:36:22,311
The next 24 to 48 hours
are really critical, but--

648
00:36:22,417 --> 00:36:24,712
We expect your father to
make a full recovery.

649
00:36:25,346 --> 00:36:27,301
Thank you so much, Dr. Burke.

650
00:36:28,195 --> 00:36:32,802
<i>First do no harm--
easier said than done.</i>

651
00:36:34,846 --> 00:36:37,680
<i>We can take all the
oaths in the world,</i>

652
00:36:38,005 --> 00:36:43,953
<i>but the fact is...
most of us do harm all the time.</i>

653
00:36:46,568 --> 00:36:48,342
I have $8 million.

654
00:36:48,816 --> 00:36:50,302
So I've heard.

655
00:36:53,276 --> 00:36:57,071
- I can... do anything I want.
- Just about.

656
00:36:59,536 --> 00:37:02,462
And all I really want to do
is a running whip stitch.

657
00:37:05,137 --> 00:37:07,381
My first year as an intern,

658
00:37:07,546 --> 00:37:10,362
I had a stable cardiac
patient who blew out his lung

659
00:37:10,517 --> 00:37:12,542
while I was transporting
him to C.T.

660
00:37:13,185 --> 00:37:14,581
I called in the code.

661
00:37:14,738 --> 00:37:17,313
By the time everyone got there,
he was dead.

662
00:37:18,265 --> 00:37:20,953
If I had put a chest
tube in right away...

663
00:37:22,325 --> 00:37:23,931
you made a mistake.

664
00:37:25,707 --> 00:37:31,180
But I stayed.
I worked. I learned.

665
00:37:33,205 --> 00:37:35,632
I never made that
mistake again.

666
00:37:36,375 --> 00:37:44,003
If I had quit, all I would have
had was that life... that I lost.

667
00:37:45,575 --> 00:37:48,201
Instead, I get to save lives.

668
00:37:49,347 --> 00:37:53,060
Every day, I get to save lives.

669
00:37:53,537 --> 00:37:56,172
<i>Sometimes even when
we're trying to help...</i>

670
00:37:56,908 --> 00:37:58,750
<i>we do more harm than good...</i>

671
00:38:06,248 --> 00:38:07,542
She told you.

672
00:38:12,455 --> 00:38:16,603
I've known you my whole life. I grew up
with you, so I know what you're thinking...

673
00:38:18,845 --> 00:38:21,462
That there is a year
of your life wasted

674
00:38:22,645 --> 00:38:26,293
trying to make it work with Addison,
and you could've been with Meredith,

675
00:38:26,725 --> 00:38:28,860
that you could be
happy right now,

676
00:38:29,855 --> 00:38:31,492
that all this...

677
00:38:32,898 --> 00:38:34,302
everything...

678
00:38:36,865 --> 00:38:39,583
that you and Meredith
could've had a real chance.

679
00:38:41,606 --> 00:38:43,071
Still...

680
00:38:47,028 --> 00:38:53,690
I thought you should know the truth. I
thought I owed you that... as a friend.

681
00:38:54,448 --> 00:38:55,813
You're not my friend.

682
00:38:59,877 --> 00:39:02,691
<i>And then the guilt
rears its ugly head.</i>

683
00:39:04,508 --> 00:39:07,470
<i>What you do with that
guilt is up to you.</i>

684
00:39:09,116 --> 00:39:11,031
Babysitting, Dr. Bailey?

685
00:39:11,266 --> 00:39:14,371
That's right. I'm babysitting.

686
00:39:14,547 --> 00:39:18,540
I'm being all unprofessional
and emotionally involved

687
00:39:18,757 --> 00:39:22,231
while my patient and her husband
are having a moment together.

688
00:39:23,755 --> 00:39:26,013
Oh, you might want
to leave now.

689
00:39:26,185 --> 00:39:28,741
I'm feeling a rush of
hormones coming on.

690
00:39:28,827 --> 00:39:30,571
There's no telling
what I might do.

691
00:39:36,088 --> 00:39:37,281
How's it going in there?

692
00:39:37,378 --> 00:39:39,501
I think they're leaning
towards a mastectomy.

693
00:39:39,537 --> 00:39:40,663
Well, that's good.

694
00:39:41,617 --> 00:39:46,670
Uh, about Izzie...
I didn't do anything.

695
00:39:46,777 --> 00:39:50,002
I know, Karev. You didn't do anything.
You weren't even here.

696
00:39:50,126 --> 00:39:53,190
No, listen... I knew.

697
00:39:53,375 --> 00:39:56,920
Izzie told me what she was gonna do,
but I didn't want to get involved.

698
00:39:57,557 --> 00:40:02,500
I didn't do anything. I didn't do anything
to stop her. You weren't the only one.

699
00:40:04,387 --> 00:40:09,103
Alex. Thank you.

700
00:40:14,377 --> 00:40:16,242
We're left with a choice...

701
00:40:21,226 --> 00:40:25,112
I got fried chicken--
extra crispy-- coleslaw,

702
00:40:25,317 --> 00:40:29,933
peach cobbler,
"beetle jump" and...

703
00:40:32,665 --> 00:40:34,823
"samurai ambush."

704
00:40:35,365 --> 00:40:38,962
The other night... when I told
you I was done trying to compete?

705
00:40:39,035 --> 00:40:40,891
That was me breaking
up with you.

706
00:40:41,848 --> 00:40:43,150
No.

707
00:40:44,296 --> 00:40:46,652
No, I think I would've
noticed that.

708
00:40:47,026 --> 00:40:51,922
Except you didn't...
which is why I broke up with you.

709
00:40:54,975 --> 00:40:57,910
<i>At least now you don't have
to feel guilty anymore.</i>

710
00:40:59,777 --> 00:41:01,351
Shut up.

711
00:41:01,887 --> 00:41:04,721
<i>Either let the guilt throw you back into the behavior</i> 

712
00:41:04,775 --> 00:41:07,081
<i>that got you into trouble in the first place</i>

713
00:41:08,868 --> 00:41:16,922
<i>or... learn from the guilt
and do your best to move on.</i>

714
00:41:17,667 --> 00:41:21,473
Are you seriously not going
to deposit that check?

715
00:41:24,927 --> 00:41:27,201
Some good needs to
come from this money.

716
00:41:27,338 --> 00:41:31,951
Until I don't know what that good is,
no, I'm not depositing the check.

